        h1(id="mission").text-center.masthead-heading.mb-0 What we do
        section
            .container.px-5
                .row.gx-5.align-items-center
                    .p-5
                        p(font-size= 48,font-weight=700)
                            | Comrat bridges the gap between education and mental health, promoting a balance between a student’s competing personal and professional goals. GCSE students and above can form a relationship with their own personal assistance pet (PAP) through checking in on it once a day and allowing it to check in on them. This symbiotic relationship encourages the user to continuously return the application due to the emotional attachment with their pet. Through accessing the app’s three areas of focus, Personal, Professional, and Mental Health, they will converse with their PAP, planning and celebrating goals.<br /><br />
                            | There is a clear need for accessible mental health support, and Comrat aims to bridge the gap between education and mental health for GCSE students and above. By forming a relationship with their own personal assistance pet (PAP), students can check in on it daily, and it will check in on them, encouraging them to return to the app and engage with its three areas of focus: Personal, Professional, and Mental Health.

